1
00:00:00,006 --> 00:00:06,006
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:04,680 --> 00:00:05,880
(Previously)
Do you like Jimmy?

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:08,000
No way!

4
00:00:08,001 --> 00:00:09,959
It's fine if you don't
want to tell me the truth.

5
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:11,400
My friends went out last night.

6
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:15,080
They know Jimmy's been hitting on me.

7
00:00:15,320 --> 00:00:16,600
My exams are coming up soon.

8
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,320
I'm thinking of turning off my phone.

9
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:23,240
If he doesn't listen, we have to let
him get hurt until he's had enough.

10
00:00:26,720 --> 00:00:28,080
Are you here to spy on me?!

11
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:30,400
Did you think I'd sneak out somewhere?

12
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,400
Don't call me. And don't come
here again for a while.

13
00:00:33,880 --> 00:00:35,640
Still clinging to my brother?

14
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:37,880
You should go ask your brother that.

15
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:40,200
The day my brother finally has enough,

16
00:00:40,520 --> 00:00:42,400
you'll end up looking
worse than a stray dog.

17
00:00:42,640 --> 00:00:45,280
And I'll be right here,
enjoying every second of it.

18
00:01:03,320 --> 00:01:04,840
What are you space cadet for?

19
00:01:05,560 --> 00:01:07,600
If I were a thief, you'd be dead by now.

20
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:10,280
I was thinking about P'Toh…

21
00:01:10,840 --> 00:01:12,360
and got carried away.

22
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:15,280
What happened this time?

23
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:17,560
Yesterday,

24
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:21,719
I think he went to see Jimmy.
I don't know what happened,

25
00:01:21,720 --> 00:01:25,239
but he looked completely drained.

26
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:26,720
That bad?

27
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:30,960
I feel so sorry for him.

28
00:01:31,320 --> 00:01:33,440
I hate seeing him like this.

29
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:39,040
Thinking about it makes me so mad.

30
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:40,840
I should beat Jimmy up.

31
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:45,280
Violence won't solve anything. The
problem is our person refuses to let go.

32
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:49,000
You're right…

33
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,560
That's why I said P'Toh
needs to hit rock bottom

34
00:01:53,200 --> 00:01:54,920
and to realize it on his own.

35
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:57,760
It's the only way.

36
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:01,240
Cold-blooded.

37
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:04,120
I didn't know my baby
could be this ruthless.

38
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,080
Wanna break up with me then?

39
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:15,400
You're scary, but I still love you.

40
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,320
We're at uni.

41
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:39,840
People are watching.

42
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,200
Promise me…

43
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:56,160
you'll never do that again.

44
00:02:57,480 --> 00:02:59,240
I can't stand it.

45
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,360
You should head back now.

46
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:24,160
I can't concentrate with you around.

47
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,360
I need to study.

48
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,400
Hello, Jim!

49
00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:50,500
"Love Alert" (Episode 6)

50
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:55,640
I just finished my exams,
so I wanted to treat you to lunch.

51
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:58,279
I can pay if you want.

52
00:04:58,280 --> 00:05:00,439
Just you asking me out makes me happy.

53
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:04,840
No way. This one is on me.

54
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:09,400
You can… treat me when my grades are…

55
00:05:10,360 --> 00:05:12,240
good enough.

56
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,040
Deal.

57
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,040
Hey, Jim.

58
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:25,000
You said you were busy today.

59
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:27,040
I am busy.

60
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:31,600
Oh,

61
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,880
This is Title, my friend from uni.

62
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,720
This is P'Toh... he's my brother's friend.

63
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,160
Man, I thought he was your boyfriend.

64
00:05:40,920 --> 00:05:43,720
Just go away already. Shoo.

65
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:54,960
Just order anything you want.

66
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,080
I'll go to the toilet for a bit.

67
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:36,040
He asked you out. It's good enough.

68
00:06:36,440 --> 00:06:39,560
Don't be petty and make him angry.

69
00:06:39,960 --> 00:06:41,520
Understand?

70
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,080
P'Toh!

71
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:56,040
What happened? Your hair is all wet.

72
00:06:56,720 --> 00:06:57,720
Oh.

73
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:02,040
Something got in my eye,
so I had to wash it out.

74
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:06,760
You should've told me. I have eye drops.

75
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,120
Using tap water…

76
00:07:09,840 --> 00:07:11,480
will make it red.

77
00:07:14,080 --> 00:07:17,080
P'Toh, I'm starving. Let's order.

78
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:30,520
Title knows Teh, and I
didn't want any drama.

79
00:07:31,400 --> 00:07:33,320
That's why I introduced you like that.

80
00:07:35,880 --> 00:07:37,960
You're not mad, right?

81
00:07:42,000 --> 00:07:44,480
No, I'm not.

82
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:49,000
I promised you I wouldn't be petty.

83
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:53,400
You're the cutest!

84
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:56,680
Let's order.

85
00:08:07,280 --> 00:08:09,160
Answer it.

86
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:12,200
Hello, Run?

87
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:14,999
Are you okay?!

88
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,879
Okay, I'm coming right now.

89
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,080
What's wrong?

90
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:21,040
My friend... is in trouble.

91
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:24,320
I'll treat you next time, okay?

92
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,560
A friend?

93
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,320
Right…

94
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:42,960
Just a friend.

95
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:54,200
Easy…

96
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:11,880
Rest here for a bit.

97
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:13,960
I'll go…

98
00:09:14,520 --> 00:09:15,680
get you something to eat.

99
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:17,760
Okay?

100
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,920
Wait, Jim…

101
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:30,680
Thank you…

102
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:34,040
for letting me stay here,

103
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:36,040
even though we're over.

104
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:41,360
Don't mention it.

105
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:46,520
It's safest for you here.

106
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:52,160
You don't have to face that
model guy and get hurt again.

107
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:00,680
Give me a sec.

108
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:05,720
Run…

109
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:10,600
I need… to take this.

110
00:10:13,120 --> 00:10:14,600
I'll be back.

111
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,640
Hello.

112
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:33,119
Jim, are you home?

113
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:36,400
Yeah. What is it, P'Toh?

114
00:10:36,680 --> 00:10:39,639
I just wanted to make sure.

115
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:42,200
And what happened?
Why did you leave so suddenly?

116
00:10:42,480 --> 00:10:43,680
Oh,

117
00:10:44,080 --> 00:10:46,839
my friend… had…

118
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:49,960
a small issue. It's all sorted now.
Everything's cleared up.

119
00:10:52,480 --> 00:10:56,000
Which friend was it? Do I know them?

120
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:57,880
What happened?

121
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,680
Why are you asking?

122
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:03,599
You're acting suspicious of me.

123
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:07,719
No, Jim. I'm not suspicious.
I'm just concerned.

124
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,639
I thought I could help.

125
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:13,119
If I wanted your help,
I would've asked for it already.

126
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:15,360
It's like you're not trusting me.

127
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:17,960
I freaking hate things like this.

128
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:20,680
Goodbye.

129
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:44,080
Was that... your new boyfriend?

130
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,320
I guess.

131
00:12:48,440 --> 00:12:51,880
He's the only one for now.

132
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:56,280
He seems... pretty jealous.

133
00:12:58,440 --> 00:13:00,759
He's like that because…

134
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:04,560
he probably loves me too much.

135
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,440
Can he…

136
00:13:08,120 --> 00:13:10,400
really put up with you?

137
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:16,880
When we were together, when I was just a
little jealous and you'd snap at me.

138
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,080
Was it jealousy or throwing a fit?

139
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:22,120
For someone like me,

140
00:13:22,440 --> 00:13:24,640
if you snap at me, I snap right back.

141
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:26,840
Stay if you can take it.

142
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:35,560
I should have been more patient.

143
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:39,999
At least...

144
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:42,320
you never laid a hand on me.

145
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:51,319
Go get some rest, Run.

146
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:55,760
I'll… handle things from here.

147
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,440
Finish eating?

148
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:21,440
Are you looking for Jimmy?

149
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:23,320
Yes.

150
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:28,560
Pour me a glass of water too.

151
00:15:33,800 --> 00:15:37,400
What are you doing here?

152
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,560
Like I told you,

153
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:54,360
I wouldn't have let him stay
here if he wasn't in trouble.

154
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,200
I understand.

155
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:02,880
Sorry for coming unannounced.

156
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:05,840
I was worried about you.

157
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:08,320
It's fine.

158
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:12,000
And... I'm sorry too, for…

159
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:14,760
snapping at you yesterday.

160
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:26,119
Actually, Jim, I...

161
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,440
Jim, are you hungry?

162
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:33,319
I can whip up that shredded chicken noodle
you love. I saw the ingredients in the fridge.

163
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:34,760
Oh, I'd love that!

164
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:38,320
I've actually been craving your cooking.

165
00:16:58,280 --> 00:17:01,000
P'Toh?

166
00:17:03,640 --> 00:17:05,160
What's wrong?

167
00:17:10,040 --> 00:17:11,600
Well…

168
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:16,959
I didn't realize you liked
shredded chicken noodles

169
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,960
made by this friend of yours.

170
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:25,240
P'Toh, we just cleared the air.

171
00:17:26,480 --> 00:17:29,480
I told you Run is just a friend.

172
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:33,360
Why are you being so sarcastic?
Stop being so petty!

173
00:18:05,480 --> 00:18:07,400
Just as good as I remember.

174
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:11,119
It's a thank you.

175
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:15,360
Tell me whenever you want some.
I can make it for you anytime.

176
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:25,760
What about your boyfriend?

177
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:28,119
Aren't you going to apologize?

178
00:18:28,120 --> 00:18:30,439
He seemed really upset.

179
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:33,240
He just walked out like that.

180
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:37,040
I never crawl back to anyone first.

181
00:18:37,880 --> 00:18:40,120
He's being that irrational.

182
00:18:40,320 --> 00:18:42,280
Definitely not.

183
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:56,920
P'Toh,

184
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:13,960
if I hadn't come home,

185
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:16,320
I wouldn't have known
you were in this state.

186
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:21,480
Don't you love yourself at all?
Why are you doing this?

187
00:20:24,360 --> 00:20:29,240
I'm sorry, Teh, for dating Jimmy in secret.

188
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:32,640
I already knew about that.

189
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,000
I didn't say anything

190
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:41,640
because I wanted you to see.

191
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:47,080
To see it with your own eyes and to realize
that Jimmy isn't good enough for you.

192
00:20:49,600 --> 00:20:51,080
He's right.

193
00:20:52,680 --> 00:20:55,160
There are plenty of fish in the sea.

194
00:20:58,720 --> 00:21:00,400
Just dump him.

195
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,160
That's a bit harsh.

196
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:09,400
But go on.

197
00:21:09,720 --> 00:21:11,240
Keep telling him.

198
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:15,080
Maybe my brother
will finally snap out of it.

199
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:21,960
Give your love to someone who deserves it.

200
00:21:22,320 --> 00:21:25,360
Don't waste it on a man like Jimmy.

201
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:28,600
He treats you like a sure thing.

202
00:21:29,200 --> 00:21:31,640
Calls you when he's hungry.

203
00:21:32,040 --> 00:21:36,040
He disappears when he's satisfied.

204
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:40,160
It's like he keeps you
as a trophy to show off.

205
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:49,240
I know you understand what's going on.

206
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:53,600
You're just struggling to let go.

207
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:22,480
Jimmy, I'm so sorry.

208
00:22:22,800 --> 00:22:27,760
(Toh: Jimmy, I'm so sorry.)

209
00:22:40,760 --> 00:22:42,760
Need something?

210
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,160
I want an extra pillow.

211
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:50,760
The sofa was too stiff last night.
I need something to prop up my legs.

212
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,320
Oh.

213
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:56,920
You should've told me.
I would've slept on the sofa myself.

214
00:22:57,280 --> 00:22:58,680
Just sleep here.

215
00:23:13,640 --> 00:23:19,200
Do you think that we can…

216
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:34,480
get back together?

217
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:45,360
(Toh: Jimmy, I'm so sorry. (Read))

218
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,600
Did you think I was gonna kiss you?

219
00:24:56,320 --> 00:25:01,080
It's time for you to leave.
You seem to be better now.

220
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:44,879
(Jimmy: If you want me
to forgive you, come over.)

221
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:47,840
(I want to hug and kiss you right now.)

222
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:55,600
(Wait for me. I'm on my way.)

223
00:26:08,447 --> 00:26:10,327
So nice.

224
00:26:10,496 --> 00:26:12,960
Huh? What's nice?

225
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:17,680
It's nice that you love…

226
00:26:18,520 --> 00:26:20,720
and always spoil me.

227
00:26:23,840 --> 00:26:27,880
Will you… love me like this forever?

228
00:26:28,920 --> 00:26:35,200
As long as you aren't mean to me,
I'll love and take care of you forever.

229
00:26:35,440 --> 00:26:36,520
Deal?

230
00:26:39,680 --> 00:26:41,520
Deal.

231
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:53,640
I feel like such a joke.

232
00:30:53,760 --> 00:30:56,680
I comfort him, and he
just runs back to that guy.

233
00:30:57,880 --> 00:31:02,480
That's irritating enough to make me cough.

234
00:31:05,800 --> 00:31:07,200
Who are you talking to?

235
00:31:08,400 --> 00:31:10,320
You're acting weird.

236
00:31:12,320 --> 00:31:15,720
P'Toh, what's so great about Jimmy?

237
00:31:16,400 --> 00:31:19,000
Why are you so head over heels for him?

238
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:24,239
I'm going to finish this cake
and go celebrate Jim's birthday.

239
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:26,280
Look after the house for me.

240
00:31:28,960 --> 00:31:30,080
Yes,

241
00:31:31,160 --> 00:31:32,840
I'll look after the house for you.

242
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:34,160
Hey!

243
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:37,000
Teh!

244
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:46,640
To learn from pain is human

245
00:31:46,893 --> 00:31:48,173
but to endure it...

246
00:31:48,760 --> 00:31:51,080
that's my brother.

247
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:57,120
It's so frustrating.

248
00:31:58,600 --> 00:32:01,360
He just has to suffer until
he hits his breaking point.

249
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:04,360
I hate seeing him hurt.

250
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:06,280
As for Jimmy...

251
00:32:07,480 --> 00:32:10,040
I don't know when he'll
stop being such a jerk.

252
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:14,520
I know he loves my brother.

253
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:16,840
He just doesn't realize it yet.

254
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:21,480
What makes you so sure he loves him?

255
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:28,000
If he didn't, he would've
ended things a long time ago.

256
00:32:28,320 --> 00:32:30,000
And if one day...

257
00:32:30,560 --> 00:32:33,120
P'Toh finally decides to walk away,

258
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:35,160
what will you do?

259
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,240
I'll be there to comfort him.

260
00:32:52,560 --> 00:32:53,560
Then…

261
00:32:53,880 --> 00:32:56,880
I'll kick Jimmy while he's down.

262
00:33:03,640 --> 00:33:04,880
Eat it.

263
00:33:25,120 --> 00:33:26,560
See you guys there.

264
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:30,040
I'll catch up with you later.

265
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:45,560
Hey, P'Toh.

266
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,600
Finished with your exams?

267
00:33:48,680 --> 00:33:51,720
Yeah, just stepped out of the exam room.

268
00:33:51,920 --> 00:33:55,600
I see. Are you going out
to celebrate with your friends?

269
00:33:57,000 --> 00:33:58,000
No,

270
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:01,120
I'm just gonna go home and sleep.

271
00:34:02,160 --> 00:34:04,160
Exams have been so exhausting.

272
00:34:04,800 --> 00:34:06,240
Is something wrong?

273
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:10,720
Nothing. I just wanted to ask.

274
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:12,800
Miss you, Jim.

275
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:14,640
Okay.

276
00:34:44,760 --> 00:34:48,320
Wow, I want a bite.

277
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:53,600
Should we sabotage
P'Toh's surprise for Jimmy?

278
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,600
I think he'd kill us both.

279
00:34:57,320 --> 00:34:59,560
I'd disown you, that's for sure.

280
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,159
That's a bit harsh.

281
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:09,160
We share the same blood. We're siblings.

282
00:35:09,640 --> 00:35:11,920
Mess with my cake then.

283
00:35:12,400 --> 00:35:13,520
You'll find out.

284
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:18,920
Want to surprise him?
You'll get a surprise yourself.

285
00:35:19,840 --> 00:35:20,840
What?

286
00:35:22,000 --> 00:35:23,480
Oh, nothing.

287
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:25,440
You should get going.

288
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:27,600
I'm leaving now.

289
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,880
Take care of the house, Teh!

290
00:35:31,480 --> 00:35:33,440
Will do.

291
00:35:35,200 --> 00:35:39,080
Why did you stop me? He's
going to find out anyway.

292
00:35:39,640 --> 00:35:43,920
He has to see it for himself, not from us.

293
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:31,360
Hungry?

294
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,440
Where's your daddy?

295
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:50,759
Hey! Nobody's going
home until we're wasted!

296
00:36:50,760 --> 00:36:51,960
Bottoms up.

297
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:46,360
Teh,

298
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:52,760
do you know where Jimmy is?

299
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:02,880
It's my birthday. Drink up, guys.

300
00:38:04,280 --> 00:38:06,199
Let's get wasted. Cheers!

301
00:38:06,200 --> 00:38:07,200
Cheers!

302
00:38:16,440 --> 00:38:17,240
What?

303
00:38:17,241 --> 00:38:19,440
Happy birthday to you.

304
00:38:19,833 --> 00:38:29,990
Happy birthday to you.
Happy birthday. Happy birthday.

305
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:35,600
Happy birthday to you.

306
00:38:36,440 --> 00:38:37,960
Happy Birthday, Jim.

307
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,320
Make a wish.

308
00:38:44,113 --> 00:38:45,593
What did you wish for?

309
00:38:45,840 --> 00:38:49,280
Wishing for another round with
the guy who brought you the cake?

310
00:38:49,760 --> 00:38:51,280
Hey, it's a secret.

311
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:53,840
If I tell you, it won't come true.

312
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:58,000
So you are wishing for another round.

313
00:38:58,880 --> 00:39:00,800
But what about the one you're dating now?

314
00:39:01,800 --> 00:39:06,479
He's not serious about that guy.
Jimmy would've introduced him to us by now.

315
00:39:06,480 --> 00:39:07,600
You've got a point.

316
00:39:07,800 --> 00:39:10,080
Shut up, you guys. I'm hungry.

317
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:12,080
My blood sugar is dropping.

318
00:39:22,360 --> 00:39:23,599
Make up, make up.

319
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:24,120
Hey, you.

320
00:39:24,121 --> 00:39:25,759
Make up, make up.

321
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:26,760
Come on.

322
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:28,279
I'm a mess now.

323
00:39:28,280 --> 00:39:30,999
Make up, make up.

324
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:33,160
It's getting everywhere.

325
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:42,960
P'Toh, wait! P'Toh!

326
00:39:43,440 --> 00:39:44,440
P'Toh!

327
00:39:44,920 --> 00:39:46,480
P'Toh!

328
00:40:01,360 --> 00:40:02,360
P'Toh, stop!

329
00:40:03,360 --> 00:40:04,360
P'Toh.

330
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:07,720
P'Toh.

331
00:40:09,280 --> 00:40:10,480
P'Toh, wait.

332
00:40:19,320 --> 00:40:21,880
Did Teh tell you I was here?

333
00:40:24,080 --> 00:40:25,080
Yes.

334
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:28,320
But he didn't tell me on his own.

335
00:40:31,240 --> 00:40:32,920
I called him

336
00:40:34,480 --> 00:40:36,720
after I didn't see you at your house.

337
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,800
I get it. I'm sorry.

338
00:40:41,400 --> 00:40:42,480
It was my fault for lying.

339
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:44,800
I'm sorry.

340
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:46,800
No.

341
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:54,320
You don't understand a thing.

342
00:41:00,880 --> 00:41:02,320
Let me ask you.

343
00:41:04,600 --> 00:41:06,880
What exactly am I to you?

344
00:41:07,600 --> 00:41:09,360
Do we have to talk about this now?

345
00:41:10,280 --> 00:41:12,319
What the hell am I to you?!

346
00:41:12,320 --> 00:41:15,520
Why are you shouting at me?
Can't we just talk normally?

347
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:27,040
Whatever I do,

348
00:41:28,400 --> 00:41:29,520
whatever I say,

349
00:41:31,200 --> 00:41:32,680
it's always wrong to you.

350
00:41:36,440 --> 00:41:37,920
Am I your partner…

351
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,520
or just someone you keep around for sex?

352
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:46,480
I think you're too emotional right now.

353
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:50,000
Oh...

354
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:52,280
really?

355
00:41:55,600 --> 00:41:57,640
Try being in my shoes, Jim.

356
00:42:00,200 --> 00:42:02,520
Just try being me for once.

357
00:42:04,873 --> 00:42:06,113
Then what do you want?

358
00:42:07,480 --> 00:42:08,720
Making a scene,

359
00:42:09,640 --> 00:42:12,160
picking a fight, being rude,

360
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:16,080
what exactly is your goal?

361
00:42:19,513 --> 00:42:21,233
I freaking hate it…

362
00:42:22,600 --> 00:42:24,320
when you act like this.

363
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:35,160
You want me to leave?

364
00:42:39,680 --> 00:42:41,080
Do you think I love you that much?

365
00:42:42,880 --> 00:42:46,560
Isn't it you who's been chasing me?
Aren't you who's the one in love?

366
00:42:50,160 --> 00:42:51,320
Let's break up.

367
00:42:53,000 --> 00:42:55,280
Let's see who's going to die first.

368
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,840
You talk like you never loved me at all.

369
00:43:03,360 --> 00:43:04,360
Yeah.

370
00:43:22,560 --> 00:43:23,680
We're through.

371
00:43:31,720 --> 00:43:32,720
Fine.

372
00:43:36,400 --> 00:43:37,640
Once we're done,

373
00:43:39,040 --> 00:43:40,760
never show your face to me again.

374
00:43:42,360 --> 00:43:44,200
Not even as friends.

375
00:44:01,080 --> 00:44:02,480
Remember what you just said!

376
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:06,240
Make sure you can actually do it.

377
00:45:26,040 --> 00:45:27,400
It's okay, Toh.

378
00:45:33,560 --> 00:45:35,240
It's just a breakup.

379
00:45:38,320 --> 00:45:41,480
You'll be fine, Toh. You'll be fine.

380
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:27,720
Slow down, Jim! You're gonna pass out!

381
00:46:28,200 --> 00:46:30,200
I want to be wasted on this crappy day.

382
00:46:33,593 --> 00:46:35,153
- Take it easy.
- What's wrong with you?

383
00:46:35,200 --> 00:46:37,000
Hey! Another round!

384
00:46:52,960 --> 00:46:54,320
Easy there.

385
00:47:07,413 --> 00:47:08,440
Hey, Jim?

386
00:48:11,360 --> 00:48:13,600
You're coming back to me, right?

387
00:48:20,520 --> 00:48:22,120
Of course, you will.

388
00:48:27,480 --> 00:48:29,240
I'll be waiting for you.

389
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:41,360
I'm sorry, P'Toh.

390
00:48:55,280 --> 00:48:56,400
(Next Episode)
P'Toh,

391
00:48:57,560 --> 00:48:59,000
why are you burning up?

392
00:48:59,560 --> 00:49:02,480
What did you do to my brother?!
He's not your toy!

393
00:49:02,760 --> 00:49:04,880
You left him to suffer with a high fever!

394
00:49:13,840 --> 00:49:14,840
Fine.

395
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:20,120
If you're gonna ghost me, let's see
who going to end up hurting more.

396
00:49:21,920 --> 00:49:25,480
Congratulations on the cafe, P'Toh.
I hope it's a huge success!
